#N canvas 827 239 734 565 12;
#X obj 393 525 r trigger_kick @hv_param 0 1 0;
#X obj 463 782 osc~ 200;
#X obj 393 636 line~;
#X obj 463 686 *~ 150;
#X obj 463 719 +~ 50;
#X obj 393 833 *~;
#X msg 393 592 1 \, 0 150;
#X obj 393 906 dac~ 1;
#X obj 175 893 s kick_dac1 @hv_param;
#X text 393 393 The trigger_ prefix creates a momentary button that triggers on press but ignores the release. This is perfect for firing drum envelopes without accidentally double-triggering when you let go., f 27;
#X text 456 591 This generates the decay envelope. When triggered \, it jumps to 1 instantly \, then fades to 0 over 150 milliseconds, f 48;
#X text 523 674 We route the envelope here to sweep the pitch of the oscillator. It scales the 0.0-1.0 envelope up to 150Hz \, adds a base pitch of 50Hz \, and sweeps the [osc~] from 200Hz down to 50Hz for a classic kick drum., f 34;
#X text 219 759 We simultaneously route the envelope down here to act as a VCA \, fading the volume out over the exact same 150ms., f 26;
#X text 175 915 Crucial: This [s kick_dac1] object is totally disconnected from the audio path. It is a 'dummy' param that tells the UI generator to position the dac~ 1 output jack at the bottom of the 'kick' column. Audio still outputs via the normal [dac~ 1] object., f 28;
#X obj 393 868 *~ 5;
#X connect 0 0 6 0;
#X connect 1 0 5 1;
#X connect 2 0 3 0;
#X connect 2 0 5 0;
#X connect 3 0 4 0;
#X connect 4 0 1 0;
#X connect 5 0 14 0;
#X connect 6 0 2 0;
#X connect 14 0 7 0;
